  "instructions": [
    "Boil the oats in a small amount of water for about 5 minutes until tender. Drain any excess water.",
    "In a skillet, heat olive oil over medium-high heat. Add minced garlic and onion, cooking for about 2-3 minutes until fragrant.",
    "Add finely diced bell pepper to the skillet, cook for another minute or two until softened slightly.",
    "Return the boiled oats to the skillet. Stir in tahini, lemon juice, salt, and pepper. Mix well.",
    "Garnish with chopped green onions if desired before serving."
